## Durable all-webhook migration runbook

Goal: move external webhook ingress from Panda to Flagg without exposing Flagg's existing web/Brain root.

### Target URLs

Use a dedicated public Funnel port for webhooks:

```txt
https://joels-mac-studio.tail7af24.ts.net:10000/webhooks/todoist
https://joels-mac-studio.tail7af24.ts.net:10000/webhooks/front
https://joels-mac-studio.tail7af24.ts.net:10000/webhooks/vercel
https://joels-mac-studio.tail7af24.ts.net:10000/webhooks/github
https://joels-mac-studio.tail7af24.ts.net:10000/webhooks/mux
https://joels-mac-studio.tail7af24.ts.net:10000/webhooks/joelclaw
https://joels-mac-studio.tail7af24.ts.net:10000/webhooks/x
```

Do **not** enable Funnel on `joels-mac-studio.tail7af24.ts.net:443`; that host already serves web/Brain paths. Funnel is public per host:port, not safely private per path.

### Phase 1 — prepare Flagg worker

```bash
cd /Users/joel/Code/joelhooks/joelclaw

# Verify X code and existing webhook tests
bun test packages/system-bus/src/webhooks/providers/x.test.ts \
  packages/system-bus/src/webhooks/providers/vercel.test.ts \
  packages/system-bus/src/webhooks/server.test.ts

pnpm exec tsc -p packages/system-bus/tsconfig.json --noEmit --pretty false
bash -n packages/system-bus/start.sh
pnpm -s brain:check

# Restart Flagg worker and re-register functions
launchctl kickstart -k gui/$(id -u)/com.joel.system-bus-worker
sleep 8
curl -fsS http://127.0.0.1:3111/webhooks | python3 -m json.tool
curl -fsS -X PUT http://127.0.0.1:3111/api/inngest >/dev/null
```

Expected `/webhooks` providers after restart:

```txt
todoist, front, vercel, github, mux, joelclaw, x
```

### Phase 2 — add Flagg public webhook Funnel safely

Generate a full Serve config from the current Flagg config and add only the webhook port:

```bash
tailscale serve status --json > /tmp/flagg-serve.before.json
python3 <<'PY'
import json
from pathlib import Path
p = Path('/tmp/flagg-serve.before.json')
config = json.loads(p.read_text() or '{}')
host = 'joels-mac-studio.tail7af24.ts.net:10000'
config.setdefault('TCP', {})['10000'] = {'HTTPS': True}
config.setdefault('Web', {})[host] = {
    'Handlers': {
        '/webhooks': {'Proxy': 'http://127.0.0.1:3111/webhooks'},
    },
}
config.setdefault('AllowFunnel', {})[host] = True
Path('/tmp/flagg-serve.webhooks.json').write_text(json.dumps(config, indent=2, sort_keys=True) + '\n')
PY

# Review before applying. This overwrites Serve config, so keep the before-file.
python3 -m json.tool /tmp/flagg-serve.webhooks.json

tailscale serve set-config /tmp/flagg-serve.webhooks.json
sleep 3
tailscale funnel status
```

Smoke tests:

```bash
curl -fsS https://joels-mac-studio.tail7af24.ts.net:10000/webhooks | python3 -m json.tool
curl -k -sS -i https://joels-mac-studio.tail7af24.ts.net:10000/ | sed -n '1,12p'
```

Expected:

- `/webhooks` returns the webhook gateway JSON.
- `/` returns Tailscale/handler 404 or equivalent, not the web app and not Brain.

Rollback for this phase:

```bash
tailscale serve set-config /tmp/flagg-serve.before.json
```

